criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age 18-70 years old;

          -  In-patient at LRCA (i.e., primary diagnosis of alcohol or drug dependence);

          -  Abstinence from alcohol and other substances of abuse for 4 days;

          -  Willingness to undergo HIV testing as per standard narcology hospital counseling and
             testing protocol or known positive HIV serostatus;

          -  Provision of contact information (e.g., name, home address, telephone number) of two
             relatives or close friends who can be contacted to share information that may be used
             to assist with follow-up;

          -  Stable address within St. Petersburg or districts within 100 kilometers of St.
             Petersburg; and

          -  Self-reported unprotected anal or vaginal sex in the last 6 months;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Not fluent in Russian;

          -  Severe cognitive impairment (Clinically apparent dementia, active psychosis, or
             severe paranoid disorder) as judged by a narcology hospital clinician and stated in
             the records;

          -  Inability to provide informed consent;

          -  Suspected or diagnosed pulmonary tuberculosis, not receiving treatment;

          -  Pending legal charges with potential impending incarceration.
